article.headline: Niagara 93, Canisius 84
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- Clif Brown came off the bench to score 25 points for Niagara as the Purple Eagles defeated Canisius 93-84 Tuesday night. Brown, averaging just seven points in his last five games, was 7-of-9 from the floor in the first half and 4-for-5 on 3-point attempts alone. Niagara (6-9, 3-4 Metro Atlantic Athletic) extended its winning streak to three while snapping a four-game road losing streak. Charron Fisher had 24 points and nine rebounds, going 12-of-18 from the free-throw line. Lorenzo Miles had 19 points and five assists for the Purple Eagles, while James Mathis had 15 points before fouling out. Kevin Downey led Canisius (4-11, 3-4) with 23 points, while Corey Herring had 20 points and six assists. Darnell Wilson also contributed 16 points. Niagara shot a blistering 60 percent in the first half, making seven 3-pointers for a 45-39 lead at halftime. Canisius trimmed the lead to three with 3:18 left and had the momentum until Brown buried a 3-point shot at the three-minute mark. Then Barry Durosier drained his only basket of the game -- a 3-pointer with 1:48 left -- for a nine-point Niagara lead.
